<p>
<seg id=1> The United States and North Korea planned to have a talk on Friday about the on-the-spot examination of a suspected place of underground nuclear facilities near Pyongyang . </seg>
<seg id=2> The delegates of the two parties will have a talk for two days in New York, and then they will continue the talk in Washington. </seg>
<seg id=3> Last month the two parties had a similar talk in Pyongyang. </seg>
<seg id=4> At the time, the talk broke down as a result of a demand presented by North Korea. </seg>
<seg id=5> North Korea demanded the US to supply 3 billion dollars as an exchange for the exminers to enter all the spots concerned for the examination. </seg>
<seg id=6> Before the new talk to be held, North Korea lauched a series of attacks on the US. </seg>
</p>
